# DreamNova Consult — Cursor Rules
# ===================================
# Ce fichier configure le comportement de Cursor AI pour ce projet.
# Design System: "SPACE CRYSTALS" — Deep space + geometric crystal shapes

## PROJECT IDENTITY
- Project: DreamNova Consult — AI Automation Agency Landing Page + Portfolio
- Team: David (founder, strategy, AI) + Alexei (social media, client outreach, learning dev)
- Partner: Ariel (50/50), Melea (tech)
- Languages: Hebrew (primary, RTL), English (LTR), French (LTR)
- Contact: dreamnovaultimate@gmail.com

## TECH STACK
- Framework: Next.js 15 (App Router, TypeScript strict)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 + CSS Variables
- i18n: next-intl (locales: he, en, fr — defaultLocale: he)
- Animations: Framer Motion (GPU-accelerated only)
- Payments: Stripe (@stripe/stripe-js) — Phase 2
- Deployment: Vercel
- Icons: lucide-react

## DESIGN SYSTEM — "SPACE CRYSTALS"
Deep space universe with floating crystal/diamond geometric elements.
Minimalist but luxurious. Dreamy but professional.

### Colors
```
--bg-deep: #06060C               /* Deep space black */
--glass-bg: rgba(255,255,255,0.04)
--glass-border: rgba(255,255,255,0.08)
--glass-highlight: rgba(255,255,255,0.12)
--accent-lavender: #8B7FFF        /* Primary — buttons, links, glow */
--accent-teal: #64DFDF            /* Secondary — tags, checkmarks */
--accent-coral: #FF8A80           /* Warm — sparingly */
--accent-gold: #FFD93D            /* Gold — sparingly */
--text-primary: #EEEEF5
--text-secondary: rgba(238,238,245,0.5)
--text-muted: rgba(238,238,245,0.3)
```

### Typography
- Display/Body (Latin): Outfit (300-800)
- Display/Body (Hebrew): Heebo (300-800)
- Monospace (stats, prices, labels): Space Mono (400-700)

### Border Radius
- Cards: 24px
- Buttons: 14px
- Pills/badges: 100px

### Glass Card Recipe
```css
background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
backdrop-filter: blur(24px);
border-radius: 24px;
/* Hover: border brighten + translateY(-4px) */
```

### Crystal Elements
- Diamond shapes: CSS squares rotated 45deg with shimmer gradient
- Slow rotation: 60s per full turn
- Sizes: 16px (particles) → 200px (hero decorative)
- Crystal text: animated gradient sweep (8s linear infinite)

### Background Layers
1. Star field: white dots at 2-4% opacity
2. Nebula orbs: 3 blurred gradient circles (lavender, teal, coral)
3. Noise texture: SVG at 2% opacity
4. Grid overlay: 80px lines at 2% opacity

### Animations (ALL GPU-accelerated — transform + opacity only)
- Scroll reveal: fadeUp, stagger 0.1s
- Card hover: translateY(-4px) + border brighten
- Crystal rotation: rotate 360deg, 60s linear
- Pulse dot: scale 1→1.3, 2s ease infinite
- Nebula float: translate ±40px, 20-30s ease infinite
- Crystal text shimmer: background-position sweep, 8s linear

## CODING RULES (TAM CODING STYLE)
1. NEVER rewrite entire files. Find the "good point" and iterate around it.
2. Code must be EXHAUSTIVE, production-ready, deployable.
3. Comments only on critical variables, zero fluff.
4. Reuse existing modules — never reinvent the wheel.
5. Mobile-first responsive (390px → 768px → 1024px → 1440px).
6. ALL text via next-intl useTranslations(), NEVER hardcoded.
7. RTL/LTR handled via dir attribute on html element.
8. Lighthouse > 90, WCAG AA.
9. CSS Variables — no hardcoded colors.
10. TypeScript strict mode.
11. Tailwind utility classes, CSS custom only in globals.css.
12. No localStorage/sessionStorage.

## FILE STRUCTURE
```
app/[locale]/layout.tsx      ← Root layout (fonts, dir, meta, providers)
app/[locale]/page.tsx        ← Main page (imports all sections)
app/[locale]/api/checkout/route.ts ← Stripe (Phase 2)
components/
  Navbar.tsx
  Hero.tsx
  Services.tsx
  Portfolio.tsx
  Pricing.tsx
  Process.tsx
  CTA.tsx
  Footer.tsx
  LanguageSwitcher.tsx
  ui/
    GlassCard.tsx
    CrystalIcon.tsx
    Button.tsx
    Badge.tsx
    SectionHeader.tsx
    CrystalParticles.tsx
messages/he.json, en.json, fr.json
styles/globals.css
lib/stripe.ts
```

## COMPONENT PATTERN
```tsx
'use client';
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';

export default function SectionName() {
  const t = useTranslations('section_key');
  return (
    <section id="section-id" className="py-24">
      <div className="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-[1200px]">
        <motion.div initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }} whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}>
          {/* content */}
        </motion.div>
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

## CURSOR-SPECIFIC INSTRUCTIONS
When you open this project:
1. Read this file first
2. Design system tokens are in styles/globals.css
3. Translations in messages/*.json
4. Your job: inject Stitch exports, polish animations, optimize
5. Check responsive at: 390px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px
6. Check RTL Hebrew alignment
7. Target Lighthouse > 90

